setup-npm-project - NPM Project Setup

USAGE:
    setup-npm-project

DESCRIPTION:
    Initialize a new NPM project with standard configuration.
    Sets up git repository, copies template files, and installs
    Babel dependencies.

PROCESS:
    1. Initialize git repository
    2. Copy .gitignore and .npmignore templates
    3. Copy package.json template
    4. Install Babel CLI, core, and preset-env
    5. Copy .babelrc.js template

NOTE:
    User should update package.json after setup.

EXAMPLES:
    setup-npm-project
